&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROTATIONAL BAND 5 PHYSIOTHERAPIST – Permanent, Fixed Term Contract, Bank &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St George’s University Hospitals NHS Foundation Physiotherapy Service is recruiting to its Band 5 Physiotherapy Rotation. We are offering the opportunity for you to work in a range of specialties. We offer a diverse range of 6 monthly rotations in the following clinical areas: Out-patients, Orthopaedics, Neurology, Neurosurgery, Stroke, Medical and Surgical wards, Cardio-thoracics, Amputees, Falls &amp; Bone Health, Senior Health, Older Peoples’ Rehabilitation, Paediatrics and Women’s Health in teams led by experienced senior therapists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St George’s is a large Teaching Hospital in South-West London, serving a diverse and multicultural local community and providing specialised services nationally. The Trust is one of Europe’s largest teaching hospitals and specialises in Major Trauma, Neurosciences, Cardiology and Plastics, amongst its specialties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have the motivation, enthusiasm and desire to develop your clinical skills, already have excellent communication skills plus the ability to work well and flexibly within a team, we would welcome your application for these posts as rotational Band 5 Physiotherapist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have a sound understanding of the NHS with at least 1 year’s NHS experience, and have experience in the core areas of Physiotherapy (undergraduate training counts).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Access to your own transport (ideally car) is essential&lt;/strong&gt; as the rotations are spread across several sites, including St George’s Hospital, Queen Mary’s Hospital, St John’s Therapy Centre and GP practices - many areas are not easily accessible by public transport.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide you with excellent clinical support from experienced clinicians in all areas, plus a structured in-service training programme to enable you to develop your clinical and professional skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Louise McGregor, Professional Lead Physiotherapy &lt;/span&gt;louise.mcgregor@stgeorges.nhs.uk &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
